laboratory_examinations.findings: MIXED BACTERIAL FLORA (>= 3 COLONY TYPES), CONSISTENT WITH SKIN AND/OR GENITAL CONTAMINATION.

Normal flow with respiratory variation in the bilateral subclavian veins; left internal jugular and axillary veins patent and compressible; left brachial, basilic, and cephalic veins patent, compressible, and show normal color flow and augmentation.
